DENGUE - VENEZUELA (07)
***********************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Dengue - Venezuela (Caracas) (04) 970924183416
Dengue - Venezuela (Caracas) (05) 970928191817
Dengue - Venezuela (Caracas) (06) 971117155031
Date: Mon, 17 Nov 1997 09:45:17 -0800
From: Dave Coder <dcoder@u.washington.edu>
Source: El Universal, Caracas, Venezuela, 17 Nov 97

Eight deaths and more than 1,700 cases of dengue have been registered in
the State of Carabobo thus far for the year, according to the Director of
Environmental Health of the State of Lara, Leornado Rangel. Despite
spraying by regional authorities, the rebound of dengue in Carabobo is seen
in the statistics of recent weeks that include the admission of 30 children
with hemorrhagic dengue to the Central Hospital of Valencia; at the same
time 6 adults are being treated in the emergency room [as outpatients?.
According to official statistics, in the southwest of the State there have
been 546 cases of which 136 [25% are hemorrhagic, while in Isabelica, in
the parish of Rafael Urdaneta, one of the most populous of that area, there
have been 501 cases. In the northern area of Valencia 201 cases have been
reported, and in the coast of Carabobo, there have been 151 cases.
An average of 10 patients present daily with dengue to the Central
University Hospital Antonio Maria Pineda de Barquisimeto, reported
Francisco Finizola, Chief of Pediatrics of the hospital. According to
Finizola, most of the patients are from neighborhoods on the northeast
margins of Barquisimeto, the most densely populated area of the city, while
some cases have come from municipalities of Palavecino and Cabudare.
Orlando Miranda, [health? chief of Zone VI, announced the beginning of a
special operation to clean the most affected areas of the capital of the
State of Lara.
